<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Petrus Mabunda, MMC for transport and planning in the City of Ekurhuleni, said:  “As the City, we strive to create enabling and inclusive environment for residents with disabilities. “Our test tour was to ensure that our buses meet a set of requirements.” Zanele Zwane, who is in a wheelchair, looked relieved when she boarded the bus. “It’s always been a challenge for me to use public transport,” she said.  “I dreaded asking people to help me to get into a taxi or a bus.  “These buses will bring so much relief to me and many other people living with different types of disabilities, because they’re easily accessible and convenient.”